"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-olympics-2024-team-gb-mens-four-rowing-bronze-medal-b1174195.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  Sport|Olympics  Team GBwon bronze in the men's four at theParis Olympics.  The quartet of Oli Wilkes, David Ambler, Matt Aldridge and Freddie Davidson got off to a poor start but produced a patient race, coming right through most of the field.  The British crew swept past Italy 800 metres from home into third place, eventually settling for bronze with the United States taking gold and New Zealand silver.  Earlier, it proved a morning of two mums at the rowing, one delighted and one disappointed.  Mathilda Hodgkins-Byrne had not been expected to win a medal but took bronze with Becky Wilde in the double sculls.  It was an impressive outcome bearing in mind Wilde had undergone surgery on both forearms back in September and getting to Paris in itself had been seen by the duo as a victory of sorts.  And then Helen Glover, unbeaten this year in the four, was surprisingly pipped to the gold. But it's a strong morning for GB with one silver and two bronze.  MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\"}"